      • annotateInnerJavaExpr

        @NotNull
private static @NotNull InnerJavaExprResult annotateInnerJavaExpr​(JMLInnerJavaExpr element,
                                                                  com.intellij.lang.annotation.AnnotationHolder holder,
                                                                  ExtraVariables extraVars,
                                                                  boolean mustReturnBoolean,
                                                                  boolean doTypeChecking)
        Recursively checks that the java expression is valid, and internally replaces JML expressions with corresponding Java expressions such that the Java resolver does not error and checks with the correct types
        Parameters:
        element - the inner java expression
        holder - the Annotation holder
        extraVars - an Object that holds extra variables that the Java resolver would not be able to resolve
        mustReturnBoolean - if true, it is checked that the expression returns a boolean value
        doTypeChecking - whether type checking needs to happen, as not all expressions need that
        Returns:
        whether the expression is valid, the text and the type of the expression and the range changes
